  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing protection of at-risk and marginalized refugees in Turkey through improved access to services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Diakonie Katastrophenhilfe (DKH) has been responding regionally to the Syrian crisis since 2012. Through its partner Support to Life (STL) in Turkey, DKH has provided emergency assistance ranging from food aid and NFI distributions to cash based interventions, psychosocial support and case management. The humanitarian protection framework recognizes every individual&apos;s fundamental rights and the obligation of state and humanitarian actors to remove any obstacles to accessing the rights to identity and documentation, right to health, education and to live free of discrimination. In Turkey, state institutions still lack adequate capacities and resources as well as services vary significantly from place to place and without the necessary language skills, information and awareness refugees continue to face difficulties in accessing services, or face protection risks. STL will support refugees&apos; access to services via provision of specialized and non-specialized support, improved capacities of government and non-government service providers and empowered community members. Based on vulnerability criteria, selected individuals will be assisted to overcome obstacles through information provision and supported in accessing services as per their right under the Temporary and International Protection Regime. Community volunteers will be trained to provide information, identify and refer cases. State service providers will receive training and support to increase their capacities. Additionally, information about service availability and challenges will feed into the analysis of protection services and will be used for advocacy towards stakeholders. Starting from March 2020, the Covid-19 pandemic effected not only public health and livelihoods but also vulnerable populations on access to basic rights and service and enhanced the protection risks. STL will provide one time cash assistance based on predetermined criteria in order to address immediate protection risks.</narrative>
  </description>
